files = list.files(dird)
myconvert = function(xl) {
  if(stringr::str_ends(xl, "XLS") | stringr::str_ends(xl, "xls")){
    v=try(readxl::read_xls(paste0(dird, xl)), silent = TRUE)
  }
  else{
    v = NA
  }
  v
}

Find c in density problem

Let c be a constant and consider the density function for the random variable Y: \[ f(y) = \begin{cases} c(2-y) \quad \text{if } 0\leq y \leq 1\\ 0 \quad \quad \quad \quad \text{elsewhere} \end{cases} \] Find the value of c. \[c\int_{0}^{1} (2-y) \,dy = 1\] \[c (2y-\frac{y^2}{2}) \Big|_{0}^{1} = 1\] \[c (2*1-\frac{1^2}{2})-(2*0-\frac{0^2}{2}) = 1\] \[c(2-\frac{1}{2}) = 1\] \[c = 1 * \frac{2}{3}\]

2/3
## [1] 0.6666667

Integral calculator: https://www.integral-calculator.com/

Find probabilities

\(X\)~\(Bin(n=10, p=1/3)\) \(Y\)~\(Normal(\mu=5, \sigma=2)\)

Discrete probabilities

Endpoints matter

\(P(X \ge 6)\)

1-pbinom(5, 10, 1/3)
## [1] 0.07656353

\(P(X < 8)\)

pbinom(7, 10, 1/3)
## [1] 0.996596

\(P(2 \leq X \leq 7)\)

pbinom(7, 10, 1/3)-pbinom(1,10,1/3)
## [1] 0.8925469

Continuious probabilities

Endpoints don’t matter

\(P(Y \ge 6)\)

1-pnorm(6, 5, 2)
## [1] 0.3085375

\(P(Y < 8)\)

pnorm(8, 5, 2)
## [1] 0.9331928

\(P(2 \leq Y \leq 7)\)

pnorm(7, 5, 2)-pnorm(2, 5, 2)
## [1] 0.7745375

Use MGF’s

Mean

\[E(y) = \mu\] \[ f(y) = \begin{cases} \frac{3}{500}(25-y^2) \quad \text{if } -5\leq y \leq 5\\ 0 \quad \quad \quad \quad \quad \quad \text{elsewhere} \end{cases} \] \[f(y) = \frac{3}{500} (25-y^2) \,dy\] \[E(y) = \mu = \frac{3}{500} \int_{-5}^{5} (25y-y^3) \,dy\] Then solve MEAN

3/500*((25*(5)^2/2-(5)^4/4)-(25*(-5)^2/2-(-5)^4/4))
## [1] 0

Variance

\[E(y^2) = \frac{3}{500} \int_{-5}^{5} (25y^2-y^4)\] Then solve E(y^2)

(3/500*((25*(5)^3/3-(5)^5/5)-(25*(-5)^3/3-(-5)^5/5)))
## [1] 5

Solve for V(y)

(3/500*((25*(5)^3/3-(5)^5/5)-(25*(-5)^3/3-(-5)^5/5)))-(3/500*((25*(5)^2/2-(5)^4/4)-(25*(-5)^2/2-(-5)^4/4)))^2
## [1] 5

Note: \[V(y) = \sigma^2 = E(y^2)-\mu^2 = 5 - 0^2 = 5\] \[V(Y) = V(3X+4) =E ((3X+4-(3μ+4))^2)\] \[= E((3X-3μ)^2)=E(9(X-μ)^2)\] \[= 9*E((X-μ)^2)=9*V(X)=18\]
